<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Asyut Governorate Divided Into 4 Security Zones </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Asyut Governorate Divided Into 4 Security Zones </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2703193094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1817 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2703193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Mar (MENA)--Interior Minister Hasan 
al-Alfi has decided to divide Asyut Governorate into four zones, 
each of which will be supervised by an officer with the rank of 
major general. 
  The minister also decided to appoint two deputies to the 
director of Asyut security to facilitate the issuance and 
following up of decisions. 
  The decision falls within the context of the security 
strategy pursued by the Interior Ministry in view of the 
geographical terrain and social nature of Asyut Governorate. 
  The interior minister's decision also took care to bolster 
the Asyut security directorate with a group of highly trained 
officers to meet current security needs. 
  Minister al-Alfi met earlier today with the new commands 
that 
have moved to Asyut Governorate and instructed them on security 
operations there. 
  The minister also issued a decision to set up four public 
directorates in the prison authority and to upgrade the latter 
into a department. 
  These directorates have been bolstered by commanding 
officers 
who enjoy a high level of security performance. 

</TEXT>

