<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Not To Participate in Cairo Fair </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel Not To Participate in Cairo Fair </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0104072294 Cairo AL-'ARABI in Arabic 28 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC0104072294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-'ARABI </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has backed down on its decision to 
allow Israel to participate in the Cairo International Fair 
scheduled to open on 9 April because of the overwhelming anger 
that swept through Egypt after the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre 
in Hebron. 
  Engineer Hamid 'Atwah, director of the fair authority, said 
Israel will not participate in the fair through its own pavilion 
or through the U.S. pavilion. Israel has not participated in 
the fair since 1986, following the attack that the "Egypt's 
Revolution" organization launched on the Israeli pavilion in 
1985. 
  Two weeks ago AL-'ARABI quoted diplomatic sources, as well 
as 
fair sources, as saying that the government was inclined to 
allow Israel to participate in the fair by allocating space for 
it in the U.S. pavilion. 

</TEXT>

