<H3> <TI>   Islamic Group Urges Austria Not To Honor Rushdie </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Islamic Group Urges Austria Not To Honor Rushdie </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3103135994 Cairo AL-AHRAM in Arabic 27 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC3103135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHRAM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Council for Call and Relief yesterday 
denounced the Austrian government's intention to grant its 
European Literature Prize to Indian-born British author Salman 
Rushdie for his book The Satanic Verses. 
  In a statement it issued, the Council said that the panel of 
judges' choice of The Satanic Verses as an example of 
contemporary European literature is a shock that arouses 
feelings and shows a clear bias and vile prejudice on the part 
of the atheists and apostates. It appealed to the Austrian 
Government to reject the panel's choice. 
  The Austrian Ministry of Education and Arts has proposed 
that 
the prize be not awarded publicly, while Arts Minister Rudolf 
Scholten refused to hand it over in secret and postponed the 
award ceremony. 

</TEXT>

