<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th: Withdrawal From Gaza, Jericho Started </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th: Withdrawal From Gaza, Jericho Started </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0204170894 Cairo ESC Television in Arabic 1600 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0204170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo ESC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political adviser to the 
Palestinian president, has affirmed that the Israeli withdrawal 
from Gaza and Jericho has actually begun and vanguards of the 
Palestinian police will deploy there within a week. 
  This follows the agreement reached by the Palestinian and 
Israeli sides on security arrangements for Hebron in the wake of 
the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. The agreement provides for the 
deployment of 160 international observers to oversee the 
arrangements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

