<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Committee Delegates Begin Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Committee Delegates Begin Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israeli Delegation Arrives </H4>

<F P=102> TA0304085694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 3 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0304085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli delegation to the talks with the 
Palestinians has arrived in Cairo. The delegation is composed 
of Major General 'Uzi Dayan, Brigadier General Yom-Tov Sami', 
Brig. Gen. Tzvi Stauber, and the Foreign Ministry's legal 
adviser Yo'el Singer. 
  Military sources told our correspondent Karmela Menashe that 
the major obstacles in the discussions with the Palestinians 
have been removed and Israel can now meet the original timetable. 
  Sufyan Abu-Zayidah, one of the Fatah leaders in the Gaza 
Strip, told Qol Yisra'el this morning that the violent incidents 
in the Gaza Strip were unconnected to the progress made in the 
peace negotiations. In his opinion, once the IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] withdraws and the Palestinian police force 
assumes responsibility for maintaining public order, the police 
will impose their authority on the entire Palestinian 
population, including the members of Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

