<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Committee Delegates Begin Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Committee Delegates Begin Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th on Meeting 13 Apr Deadline </H4>

<F P=102> TA0304155094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 3 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0304155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Cairo, Israeli and Palestinian delegations led 
by General 'Uzi Dayan and Dr. Nabil Sha'th today resumed 
negotiations on Palestinian autonomy in Gaza and Jericho. 
  Gen. Dayan, who heads the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
Planning Branch, told reporters that Israel hoped the 
negotiations would be completed quickly. 
  Nabil Sha'th told Qol Yisra'el's correspondent in Cairo Arye 
Gus the PLO want to conclude the agreement by the 13 April 
deadline in the Declaration of Principles. 
  [Begin Sha'th recording] We are starting the negotiations on 
the withdrawal plan from Gaza and Jericho, which is really the 
completion of what we had started and stopped just because of 
the massacre. We hope to finish as soon as possible the 
withdrawal plan, the deployment of the Palestinian police force, 
and the remaining factors of security in the Gaza and Jericho. 
The entry of the Palestinian police force will start with first 
a small group of maybe seven or eight people to go to make the 
arrangements and then be followed by a larger number to take 
over some of the camps and to start preparing within a week at 
most, maybe Thursday. There will be a detailed schedule that 
will coincide with gradual withdrawal of the Israeli Armed 
Forces, so that by the end of this period the Palestinian police 
force will be fully deployed. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

