<H3> <TI>   Arab Maghreb Union Presidential Council Meets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Maghreb Union Presidential Council Meets </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministers Create Free Trade Zone </H4>

<F P=102> LD0304094994 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0700 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0304094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] On the sidelines of the proceedings of the Arab 
Maghreb Union [AMU] summit, an official ceremony was held 
yesterday at the Foreign Ministry during which 11 Maghrebian 
agreements on cooperation were signed. These agreements pertain 
to a number of fields, mainly the economic, cultural and trade 
sectors. The most important of these agreements is the decision 
to set up a free trade zone among the five Maghrebian countries. 
  These agreements were signed on the Tunisian side by Foreign 
Minister Habib Ben Yahya; for Algeria by Foreign Minister 
Mohamed Salah Dembri; for Morocco by Foreign Minister Abdellatif 
Filali; for Mauritania by Foreign Minister Mohamed Salem Ould 
Lekhel; for Libya by Mr. Jum'ha al-Fazzani, General People's 
Committee secretary for unity. [passage omitted: officials 
welcome signing of these agreements] 
  The Tunisian secretary of state for foreign affairs said it 
has been agreed to start the practical implementation of the 
free trade zone agreement immediately, and that a working group 
will begin preparing articles regarding this agreement as from 
the current month of April. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

