<H3> <TI>   Arab Maghreb Union Presidential Council Meets </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Maghreb Union Presidential Council Meets </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ben Ali Delivers Speech </H4>

<F P=102> LD0304162194 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1300 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0304162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Address by Tunisian President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali to </F>
Arab Magreb Union summit in Tunis on 3 April -- live or recorded] 
  [Excerpts] In the name of God, the merciful, the 
compassionate; Your Excellencies, at a time when the proceedings 
of our council are about to be concluded, I am pleased to 
express to you once more our pride at hosting this Maghreb 
meeting in which we have changed viewpoints on our joint Maghreb 
action, on the most efficient means to give a boost to the march 
of our Arab Maghreb, and on the most prominent matters and 
international issues. [passage omitted] 
  There is no doubt that any progress on the path of building 
a 
unified Maghreb is liable to add strength and competence to the 
economies of our countries for integration and positive 
interaction with the international economic community and 
achieve more equilibrium in the exchange relations with the 
large economic groups and particularly those with which we have 
traditional relations in our immediate neighborhood. [passage 
omitted] 
  At the end of my speech, your excellencies, I am pleased to 
express on your behalf and in my name most sincere 
congratulations to His Excellency President Liamine Zeroual, the 
head of state of the fraternal People's Democratic Republic of 
Algeria, on his taking over the Presidency of the Arab Maghreb 
Union this year. We are convinced that his undertaking these 
supreme tasks will give our unionist march, thanks to the wisdom 
and conviction in the Maghreb unity that characterize him, more 
impetus and progress to the course of building our Arab Maghreb 
towards achieving the common aspirations of our peoples. 
  May God's peace, mercy, and blessings be upon you. 
[applause] 

</TEXT>

