<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy Voices Appreciation for Jordan's Support </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy Voices Appreciation for Jordan's Support </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0304084694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0400 GMT 3 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0304084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian Ambassador in Amman al-Tayyib 
'Abd-al-Rahim has voiced appreciation for the Jordanian 
Government's position under Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali in support of the PLO as well as the Government's 
policy aimed to protect the Palestinian people in the occupied 
territories and establish a just and comprehensive peace in the 
region. 
  In a statement to the Jordanian news agency commenting on 
the 
remarks made by Dr. Jawad al-'Anani, minister of state for 
cabinet affairs and information minister, on the recent 
agreement reached in Cairo, 'Abd-al-Rahim said the Jordanian 
Government's call for Palestinian national unity and its support 
for the PLO, which is on the threshold of a new phase, emanate 
from a genuine pan-Arab position and show sound political 
foresight. 
  He added that the PLO is very eager to coordinate with 
Jordan 
now and in the future in view of the common interests and the 
one future for both fraternal peoples. He said: Jordan, under 
His Majesty King Husayn and his wise government, is maintaining 
a pan-Arab position. We believe this position should be 
championed because it supports the Palestinian people's struggle 
to establish an independent entity on their national soil, he 
added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

