<H3> <TI>   Fatah Hawks Urge Halt to Talks With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Hawks Urge Halt to Talks With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404071494 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR in Arabic 1 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> TA0404071494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-NAHAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By 'Imad al-Afranji] </F>
  [Text] Gaza -- The Fatah Hawks, Fatah's military 
apparatus, have called on the Palestinian leadership to stop the 
negotiations in protest of Israeli practices in the occupied 
territories. They urged the leadership not to resume the talks 
until acts of pursuit and liquidation against all wanted men 
from all factions are halted. 
  The Fatah Hawks called on the movement's organizational 
authority in the Gaza Strip to immediately freeze all channels 
of contact with the Israeli administration. 
  The statement said that this has no connection with the 
peace 
process, that what is taking place at the negotiating table is 
being done according to the laws of negotiations and what is 
taking place on the ground in the occupied territories is 
governed by the laws of the occupied territories, and that there 
was no contradiction between the two. 
  The statement was issued in the wake of the killing of six 
Fatah activists last Monday by special Israeli units. 

</TEXT>

