  [Excerpts] Riyadh, 2 Apr -- The Saudi foreign minister, 
Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal, denied today that there are differences 
of opinion between the Gulf Cooperation Council states regarding 
the stance toward the Iraqi regime. He said: "We have not 
noticed the existence of differences regarding this matter 
whether on the level of the summit or the current level," in 
allusion to the foreign ministers meeting of the states of the 
council which started its work here today under his 
chairmanship. Prince Sa'ud spoke to journalists at the end of 
the second working session of the ministers here tonight. 
[passage omitted] 

