<H3> <TI>   Salih, Omani Head Meet, Discuss Bilateral Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih, Omani Head Meet, Discuss Bilateral Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404062694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0404062694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting among brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council; His 
Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id of Oman; brother 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid, vice chairman of the Presidential Council; and His 
Highness Tuwayni Bin- Shihab, the personal representative of His 
Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin- Sa'id, was held at 2030 yesterday at 
al-Hisn Palace in Salalah in the Sultanate of Oman. 
  During the meeting, the conferees discussed brotherly 
relations between the two fraternal countries, Yemen and Oman. 
The conferees also discussed efforts under way to contain the 
political crisis and enhance unity and stability in Yemen. 
  An official round of Yemeni-Omani talks was held under 
brother Lt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and His Majesty Sultan 
Qabus Bin-Sa'id of Oman. The session was attended by members of 
the delegations of the two sides. 
  Following the joint session, brother Lt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih and His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id held a closed 
session. The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has learned that talks 
addressed the warm brotherly relations between the two fraternal 
countries and ways of enhancing them, as well as developments in 
Yemen in light of the efforts taking place to contain the 
political crisis, reactivate constitutional agencies, and 
implement the accord document. The purpose of this is to 
safeguard unity, democracy, and stability in Yemen and enhance 
security and stability in the region. 
  In addition, several regional, Arab, and world issues and 
developments were discussed, primarily issues of interest to the 
two fraternal countries. 
  His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id of Oman received in 
Salalah yesterday evening brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice 
chairman of the Presidential Council and secretary general of 
the Yemeni Socialist Party. Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid arrived 
in the Sultanate of Oman yesterday from the United Arab 
Emirates. He was received at Salalah airport by His Highness 
Tuwayni Bin-Shihab Al Sa'id, the personal representative of His 
Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id, and several other Omani 
officials. 

</TEXT>

