<H3> <TI>   Cairo Meeting Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Meeting Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0304062494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0304062494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official source at the General Committee of the 
General People's Congress [GPC], in a statement to the Yemeni 
News Agency, SABA', has expressed the GPC command's amazement at 
a report aired by the London-based Middle East Broadcasting 
Center, MBC, yesterday. The report says that brother Lieutenant 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential Council chairman and 
GPC secretary general, will meet with his deputy, brother 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid, in Cairo on 4 April. The source said that the GPC 
command knows nothing about this report, and that the brother 
chairman of the Presidential Council will pay an official visit 
to the Sultanate of Oman today, Sunday, at the invitation of his 
brother His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id. 

</TEXT>

