<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Yeltsin's Envoy Arrives </H4>

<F P=102> JN0104170694 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1510 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0104170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 1 Apr (SANA)--Igor Ivanov, Russian deputy 
foreign minister and Russian President Boris Yeltsin's envoy to 
the Middle East, and his delegation arrived in Damascus this 
afternoon. Their visit to the Syrian Arab Republic will last for 
several days. 
  Ivanov, was received at the Damascus International Airport 
by 
Raslan 'Allush, assistant to the foreign minister, director of 
Eastern Europe Desk at the Foreign Ministry, the Russian 
ambassador in Damascus, and embassy staff. 
  In a statement to the Syrian Arab News Agency's 
correspondent, Ivanov said: I am carrying a personal message to 
President Hafiz al-Asad from Russian President Boris Yeltsin. 
President al-Asad's ideas are appreciated by the Russian 
leadership, and his excellency enjoys high reputation and esteem 
in Russia. 
  He said this visit was mandated by the Russian president 
within the framework of efforts the Russian leadership is 
carrying out to overcome the situation in the region caused by 
the Hebron massacre. 
  Ivanov emphasized that Russia wants the peace process to 
continue and wants a strong and comprehensive peace to be 
realized in the Middle East. He added that Russia, in its 
capacity as a superpower and one of the sponsors of the peace 
process, has made and will continue to make all efforts toward 
reaching this objective. 
  He emphasized that Moscow attaches great importance to 
cooperation between Syria and Russia. 
  Ivanov said he will discuss in Damascus issues relating to 
the Middle East peace process in addition to bilateral relations. 
  Concluding his statement, he emphasized that the latest 
Russian initiative is valid and long term, and that its 
implementation depends on the positions of all concerned parties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-11912 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes064_o_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-064 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Al-Asad Receives Envoy </H4>

<F P=102> JN0204161594 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0204161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad received at 1230 today Igor 
Ivanov, first deputy Russian foreign minister and envoy of 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin, and his delegation. 
  The meeting was attended by Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' 
and Russian Ambassador in Damascus Aleksandr Zotov. 
  Ivanov conveyed a message to President al-Asad from 
President 
Yeltsin dealing with bilateral relations and the peace process. 
President al-Asad gave him a message in reply for President 
Yeltsin. 
  The Russian envoy spoke about his country's concern for the 
peace process in the region and its willingness to play an 
active role in this field. He also expressed his country's 
appreciation for Syria's status and its positive role in the 
region. 
  President al-Asad welcomed the willingness of Russia, which 
is one of cosponsors of the peace process, to play an active 
role to help this process advance on the path to a just and 
comprehensive peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

