  [Text] A delegation from the Iranian Majles arrived in 
Damascus this evening. The delegation is led by Dr. Hasan 
Ruhani, deputy speaker of the Majles and chairman of the Foreign 
Affairs Committee. The delegation will hold talks with the 
People's Assembly officials. 
  The delegation was received at Damascus International 
Airport 
by 'Adil Jamus, the deputy speaker of the People's Assembly; 
Shakir Is'ayyid, the head of the Arab and Foreign Affairs 
Committee; and the Iranian ambassador in Damascus. 
  Upon arrival, Dr. Ruhani said he is carrying two messages 
for 
President Hafiz al-Asad from Islamic Revolution Leader Ayatollah 
'Ali Khamene'i, and Iranian President 'Ali Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  Dr. Ruhani expressed the Iranian people's appreciation of 
the 
wise political leadership in Syria, and hailed bilateral 
relations in various fields. 

