94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0304143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Several settlement leaders in the territories said 
that in their meeting this morning, Prime Minister Rabin 
promised them not to evacuate Jews from Hebron, not to change 
the location of the Jewish neighborhoods in the town, and that 
all the settlements in the Gaza Strip, including Dugit, 
Netzarim, and Kfar Darom will remain where they are at least 
until the final settlement is implemented. 
  The settlement leaders also told our correspondent Gil 
Litman 
that the prime minister confirmed in the meeting that there has 
been a significant rise in the number of stone-throwing and 
firebomb incidents in Judaea and Samaria in recent weeks. Rabin 
told them he believes there are now five times more incidents 
than there were in the past. Mr. Rabin promised the settlement 
leaders that the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] would step up its 
activities against those who disturb the peace in the 
territories. Those attending the meeting were Uri Ari'el, 
secretary of the Council of Jewish Settlements in Judaea, 
Samaria, and the Gaza Strip; Rabbi Yo'el Bin-Nun of 'Ofra, and 
Tzvi Hendel, head of the Hof 'Aza Regional Council. 

