<H3> <TI>   Gaza Settlement Dugit `Abandoned' by Inhabitants </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaza Settlement Dugit `Abandoned' by Inhabitants </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404112094 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 4 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> TA0404112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by David Regev] </F>
  [Excerpt] Last night the residents of the Dugit settlement 
in the northern Gaza Strip abandoned their settlement and set up 
an encampment on the Israeli side of the border. The encampment 
was a protest against what they termed a deterioration in the 
state of security. 
  "We do not intend to return to Dugit any more. We fear for 
our lives. If they cannot protect us, they should compensate us 
and let us leave," two settlers, Tova Goren and Orit Qariti, 
said last night. 
  The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] and the police placed guards 
at the encampment and declared the new settlement a closed 
military zone, permitting the settlers to stay on the site till 
morning. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

