<F P=102>   TA0104182594 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1730 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0104182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1730 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Syrian Army handed over 11 Hizballah fighters 
to the Lebanese Army last night. They had been arrested about 
three weeks ago in the course of a violent demonstration to mark 
Jerusalem Day held in Ba'labakk, an area under Syrian control in 
Lebanon. 
  Uri Lubrani, coordinator of government activities in 
Lebanon, 
told our correspondent Yoram Kohen that as far as is known this 
is the first time such an event has occurred. If it is true, 
Lubrani added, this is a step in the right direction aimed at 
curbing terror in Lebanon. 

