<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Fatah member from Khan Yunus was killed this 
evening as he was assembling a bomb in the Khan Yunus refugee 
camp. The victim is Khalid Halabi, who spent eight years in an 
Israeli prison because of his Fatah membership. His body was 
snatched away from the hospital. 
  Our correspondent Shlomi Eldar adds that shots were fired 
this evening at an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] lookout position 
in al-Shaykh Radwan. Nobody was hurt. The Fatah Hawks claimed 
responsibility for this attempted terrorist attack. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1900 GMT on 2 April 
adds: "An Israeli was lightly injured in the head this evening 
when his car came under a hail of stones in the village of 
al-Jib south of Ramallah. Two border policemen were injured: 
one in Qalqilyah and another in Gaza. 
  ["Riots erupted this evening in the al-Burayj refugee camp. 
In Gaza, an explosive charge was thrown at a police station. 
The charge exploded, but nobody was hurt and no damage was 
caused. 
  ["A firebomb was thrown this evening at an Israeli car in 
the 
'Aqabat Jabr refugee camp on the outskirts of Jericho. Nobody 
was hurt and no damage was caused. The driver reported the 
incident and drove away. An IDF unit arrived on the scene and 
found the firebomb's remnants as well as empty cartridges. 
Shortly afterward, an Arab suffering serious wounds arrived in 
a hospital in the area. The security forces are checking whether 
the man was the one who threw the firebomb and was wounded by 
shots fired by passengers aboard the Israeli car."] 

</TEXT>

