<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Judge Denies LF Exonerated of Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Judge Denies LF Exonerated of Church Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0204120094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0204120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prosecutor General Magistrate Munif 'Uwaydat met 
with Judge Joseph Furayhah, judicial investigator into the 
Sayyidat al-Najat church at the Palace of Justice this morning. 
Furayhah briefed 'Uwaydat on the investigation process of the 
bombing of the church in Zuq Mikha'il. 
  After the meeting, Judge 'Uwaydat made a statement in which 
he denied a report published by the newspaper AL-DIYAR yesterday 
that he had exonerated the Lebanese Forces as an establishment 
of the charge of bombing the Sayyidat al-Najat church. He said 
the aforesaid newspaper's headlines differ from the article's 
text. He noted that what he really had said was that a judicial 
finding can only be decided on after completion of an 
investigation and will be declared subsequently in an 
indictment. He said that this rule pertains to the judicial 
procedure mechanism and does not mean anyone has been cleared, 
as the paper incorrectly concluded. 
  He regretted the use of his statement for narrow-minded 
political purposes and as a pretext for a defense in the media 
aimed at detouring the investigations from their natural course. 
He noted that we need to continue the investigations in an 
objective atmosphere and in strict secrecy free from distortions 
of facts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

