<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Criticizes `Terrorist' Decision on Media </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hizballah Criticizes `Terrorist' Decision on Media </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404104194 Beirut AL-NAHAR in Arabic 2 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-NAHAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah has 
said that the government has silenced national and Islamic 
media, which support security measures and peace. He urged the 
government to rescind its decision immediately. 
  Nasrallah was addressing a memorial for Hajj 'Abdallah 
Mi'mah 
in Al-Laylaki Mosque yesterday. The service was attended by 
'Ammar al- Musawi, Hizballah deputy Political Bureau chairman; 
Deputies Muhammad Ra'd, Muhammad Funaysh, and 'Ali 'Ammar; and 
some ulema. Nasrallah said: Government officials have 
repeatedly sought to oppress the media. We even hear dissonant 
voices today calling for additional controls on the printed 
media, which thought the publication law protected them from 
oppression. These voices are also demanding control over 
printing houses. 
  He added: People in Lebanon feel annoyed and suffocated by 
this. The government was not wise in making this decision. 
Indeed, it was opportunistic because it used the political and 
security situation to pass the plan. Like all forces, trends, 
and all the Lebanese people, we call on the political authority 
to rescind this unfair and terrorist measure and to promptly 
pass the media law. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

