<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Syrian Construction Minister Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syrian Construction Minister Pays Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With al-Hariri </H4>

<F P=102> JN0104173494 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0104173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanese Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri received in 
Beirut today, Majid 'Izzu Ruhaybani, the Syrian minister of 
reconstruction and building, and his delegation who arrived in 
Beirut this morning. 
  Talks centered on bilateral relations, historical links, and 
existing ties between the two countries and ways to bolster them 
to realize joint aims and interests. 
  In a statement to reporters, the minister emphasized 
continued Syrian support of Lebanon's march to entrench its 
national unity, rebuild it, and support its struggle to liberate 
its occupied territory. 
  The minister said: At President Hafiz al-Asad's 
instructions, Syria is always prepared--prompted by its 
brotherly feelings--to implement any projects by Syrian general 
construction companies if Lebanon needs them. Ruhaybani alluded 
to schools constructed in southern Lebanon by Syrian companies 
in cooperation with the higher committee in support of the 
south. He said: We are prepared to contribute to reconstructing 
Lebanon within the framework of the close brotherly cooperation 
between the two countries. 
  This afternoon, Ruhaybani and his delegation held meetings 
with Dr. Hasan Yusuf, head of the council of the south, and the 
council's members. They discussed joint work to implement 
services projects being implemented in southern Lebanon by joint 
financing of the Syrian committee of solidarity with the people 
of the south and by the council of the south. Discussion also 
dealt with aspects of future cooperation and ways to support the 
people of southern Lebanon and western al-Biqa' to confront the 
repeated and bestial Israeli attacks. 
  Dr. Hasan Yusuf, chairman of the council of the south, 
praised Syria's continuous assistance to the people of the 
south, under President Hafiz al-Asad, to ensure the means of 
their steadfastness in the face of the Israeli occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

