<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Patriarch Assails State's Attitude Toward Christians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Patriarch Assails State's Attitude Toward Christians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0104181194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0104181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Maronite Patriarch Mar Nasrallah Butrus Sfayr stated 
that the Christians' abstention from taking part in the state's 
activities is due to the imbalance in the distribution of roles 
following the settlement accord that put an end to the war. He 
pointed out that the state has not treated everyone equally and 
has failed to make Christians feel that it cares about them as 
much as other citizens. 
  He noted that except for faith in God, freedom is Lebanon's 
one and only asset. He pointed out that all complaints reflect 
violations of the principle of national accord. 
  Patriarch Sfayr's remarks came in his Easter message to the 
Lebanese today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-11976 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes064_n_94010" </HT>


