<DATE1>  3 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Christian Presence in Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Views Christian Presence in Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0304075194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0700 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0304075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following his meeting with Maronite Patriarch Mar 
Nasrallah Butrus Sfayr in Bkirki yesterday, Minister of State 
Jean 'Ubayd spoke about three issues. The first of these deals 
with the Christian representation [in state institutions]. He 
stressed that there is such representation, as reflected in the 
presence of the Franjiyah, Mu'awwad, and Buwayz families. No 
one can dispute their patriotism and nationalism, he stressed. 
  As for the Christian figures living abroad, Minister 'Ubayd 
said that Raymond Iddih himself chose to leave and so did 
General Michel 'Awn and former President al-Jumayyil. Gen. 'Awn 
can return at any time but must do so in accordance with the 
law, 'Ubayd added. 
  Concerning the third issue, Minister 'Ubayd said: I am 
against a Muslim state or a Christian state. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

