<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israelis Reportedly Offer To Withdraw Within 4 Days </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israelis Reportedly Offer To Withdraw Within 4 Days </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0204101694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0925 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0204101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 2 Apr (MENA) -- High-ranking Palestinian 
sources taking part in the autonomy talks have said that the PLO 
has received an Israeli offer to withdraw from Gaza and the 
Jericho area within four days. According to the sources, 
Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres reiterated this in 
statements to the Israeli television yesterday. 
  The sources add that a number of Palestinian deportees have 
left Tunis for the homeland after Israel has agreed to let 35 
deportees return. 
  Palestinians arriving from the occupied territories have 
said 
that the Israeli Army command plans to organize the process of 
transferring control to the Palestinian national authority 
before withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho and that the Israeli 
Army started to evacuate the camp and withdraw much equipment 
from the Gaza Strip a few days ago. 
  The Palestinian sources note that the occupation army's 
senior officers estimate that the army will be prepared to 
complete its withdrawal within 72 hours of receiving orders to 
withdraw. 
  According to Palestinian sources in Tunis, 300 of the 
Palestine Liberation Army's senior officers will enter Gaza and 
Jericho to take over control once the expected Israeli 
withdrawal is completed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-11981 </DOCNO>
