<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat's Cairo Visit Postponed Due to Engagements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat's Cairo Visit Postponed Due to Engagements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0304142094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1403 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0304142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Apr (MENA)--An official Palestinian source 
has told MENA that the visit to Cairo by Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat has been postponed to Tuesday [5 April] or 
Wednesday. 
  The source pointed out that the postponement is due to 
Egyptian and Palestinian engagements. 
  'Arafat was expected to arrive in Cairo this evening or 
tomorrow morning for consultations with President Husni Mubarak 
and senior Egyptian officials on the ongoing peace negotiations 
with Israel in Cairo to pave the way for implementing the 
Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
  The agreement is expected to be signed in Cairo before 13 
April. 

</TEXT>

