<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir, U.S. Envoy Meet; Foreign Minister Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir, U.S. Envoy Meet; Foreign Minister Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0104191294 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 0430 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0104191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The president of the Republic, Lieutenant General 
'Umar Hasan Ahmad al-Bashir, yesterday evening at the republican 
palace, met Mrs. Madeleine Albright, the United States permanent 
ambassador to the United Nations, who arrived in the country 
yesterday afternoon on a brief visit. 
  In a statement issued after the meeting, the U.S. envoy 
stressed that her discussions with Lt. Gen. al-Bashir were 
serious, open, and clear, and that the dialogue was very 
important. 
  For his part, Foreign Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih, 
who 
attended the meeting, expressed Sudan's satisfaction with the 
visit by the U.S. envoy, which is considered the real beginning 
of a serious dialogue between Sudan and America. He pointed out 
that dialogue was a course which had been followed, and had been 
called for, by the revolution from the outset. He said: We 
believe that we have entered preliminary negotiations, and that 
the revolution is working for peace. We call upon all sides to 
work for a just and lasting peace. 

</TEXT>

