<H3> <TI>   Four Political Parties Hold Meeting on Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Political Parties Hold Meeting on Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0304125094 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0304125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The national radio has learned that four political 
parties -- the National Liberation Front [FLN], the Islamic 
Society Movement [HAMAS], the Islamic Nahda [Movement] Party, 
and the Movement for Democracy in Algeria -- are meeting today 
to coordinate their stances regarding the dialogue resumed by 
President Lamine Zeroual, with political parties, national 
figures, and social and economic organizations, especially after 
the presidency official spokesman's meeting with the national 
press. 

</TEXT>

