<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Over 300 Foreigners Arrested in Tamanrasset </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over 300 Foreigners Arrested in Tamanrasset </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2703224294 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703224294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The security servives in the province of Tamanrasset 
today announced that they have arrested more than 300 people of 
foreign nationality during the combing operations which the 
security forces recently carried out in a number of quarters of 
the capital of Hoggar. The security services added that those 
persons were residing illegally in Algeria. The services 
pointed out that most of those arrested are perverts who carry 
out unlawful practices, including trading in drugs and armed 
robbery, as well as money dealings, as they have not presented 
any identity documents. During this day-long combing operation, 
in which joint forces of the army, police, gendarmerie, and 
customs participated, more than 1100 tins of Lahda [powdered] 
milk and baby milk, and more than 2000 packs of cigarettes - all 
of which were going to be smuggled to neighboring states - were 
seized. 

</TEXT>

