  [Text] Cairo, 4 Apr (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak held a 
round of talks with Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad this 
afternoon at the presidential palace in al-Qubbah. 
  The talks were attended on the Egyptian side by Prime 
Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi, Defense Minister Field Marshal 
Muhammad Husayn Tantawi, Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa, Information 
Minister Safwat al- Sharif, and Egypt's Ambassador to Syria 
Mustafa 'Abd-al-'Aziz. 
  On the Syrian side, the talks were attended by Syrian Vice 
President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddamm, Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar', and Syria's Ambassador in Egypt 'Isa Darwish. 

