<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Syrian President Arrives for `Surprise' Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syrian President Arrives for `Surprise' Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Egyptian Envoy Comments </H4>

<F P=102> NC0404151794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1315 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 4 Apr (MENA)--Dr. Mustafa 'Abd-al-'Aziz, 
Egypt's ambassador to Damascus, has made a statement at the 
conclusion of the first round of talks between President Husni 
Mubarak and Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad in Cairo today. He 
pointed out that the two Arab leaders are discussing the various 
aspects of the peace process and the obstacles facing it, since 
it is a major and pivotal issue. He added that the two leaders 
are also discussing a number of other issues of common interest 
as well as some pan-Arab issues, including the situation in 
Yemen and the ongoing efforts to achieve stability there. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz added that the two presidents will meet 
again this evening to complete their discussion of issues of 
common interest. During the evening session, the two leaders 
are expected to review all matters related to bilateral 
relations between the two countries and assess what has been 
achieved during the meetings of the Egyptian-Syrian higher joint 
committee, he added. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-'Aziz described Egyptian-Syrian relations as 
excellent and said they are proceeding normally with no 
problems. Every now and then, he added, these ties need to be 
reviewed to give them momentum. 
  President Mubarak will host a dinner banquet in honor of 
President al-Asad and his accompanying delegation this evening. 
The two leaders are expected to hold a news conference at the 
end of their talks, which may last until tomorrow morning. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-12002 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes065_c_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-065 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Syrian President Arrives for `Surprise' Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syrian President Arrives for `Surprise' Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mubarak, al-Asad Meet Privately </H4>

<F P=102> NC0404193394 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1830 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0404193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Presidents Husni Mubarak and Hafiz al-Asad resumed 
their talks at a closed meeting in the Presidential Office this 
evening. 
  Information Minister Safwat al-Sharif has stated that the 
two 
leaders resumed their talks on developments in the peace process 
and ongoing contacts among the Arab parties, Israel, and the 
parties concerned with the Middle East issue. 
  He added that the talks dealt with the Arab stance and 
regional and international issues, including the situation in 
Somalia and recent developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The information minister added that the summit talks 
reflected the identical views of both leaders on regional and 
world issues and were marked by mutual understanding and a 
desire to serve the greater Arab interests. 
  The closed meeting continued for two hours and 15 minutes, 
after which the members of the Syrian and Egyptian delegations 
joined the two leaders in an expanded meeting. 
  The two leaders later resumed their talks over a dinner 
banquet hosted by President Mubarak for Syrian President Hafiz 
al-Asad and the accompanying delegation. Senior state officials 
attended the dinner. 
  The Egyptian and Syrian delegations held talks cochaired by 
Syrian Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam and Prime Minister 
Dr. 'Atif Sidqi. The talks dealt with convening the 
Egyptian-Syrian Higher Committee and the issues that will be 
discussed within the framework of strengthening bilateral 
cooperation. The two sides also assessed the progress made 
recently in several areas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

