<H3> <TI>   Syrian President Arrives for `Surprise' Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syrian President Arrives for `Surprise' Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Damascus Radio Details Cairo Talks </H4>

<F P=102> JN0504081494 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0415 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0504081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Presidents Hafiz al-Asad and Husni Mubarak yesterday 
convened three sessions of talks, one closed, to discuss the 
Middle East peace process, and the efforts being made to achieve 
the objective set for it. They also discussed Arab and world 
issues. The following message from the media team accompanying 
President al- Asad on his Egyptian visit: 
  [Begin recording] Their Excellencies Presidents Hafiz 
al-Asad 
and Husni Mubarak held a closed session at 1900 Damascus time 
yesterday at the permanent headquarters of the Egyptian 
Presidency. This was followed by a plenary session attended, 
alongside the presidents, by Syrian Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim 
Khaddam, Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', and Dr. 'Isa Darwish, 
the Syrian ambassador in Cairo. The talks were also joined by 
Egyptian Prime Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi, Information Minister 
Safwat al-Sharif, Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa, and Dr. Mustafa 
'Abd-al-'Aziz Mursi, Egypt's ambassador in Damascus. 
  The presidents had held an expanded session upon the arrival 
of President al-Asad in Cairo yesterday afternoon. Syrian Vice 
President Khaddam, Foreign Minister al-Shar', and the Syrian 
ambassador in Cairo attended the talks. Egyptian Prime Minister 
Dr. 'Atif Sidqi, Defense Minister Marshal Muhammad Husayn 
Tantawi, Information Minister Safwat al-Sharif, Foreign Minister 
'Amr Musa, and the Egyptian ambassador in Damascus attended the 
meeting. 
  The three sessions considered the peace process and the 
efforts being made to promote its set objective and contacts 
being undertaken to advance that goal. Arab and international 
issues, including those related to the Nonaligned Movement, were 
also discussed. 
  President Mubarak last night hosted a dinner banquet at the 
Egyptian Presidency for President al-Asad and his delegation, to 
which top Egyptian civilian and military officers were invited. 
  President al-Asad arrived in Cairo at 1345 yesterday. The 
Egyptian president led the welcoming party at the airport. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

