<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Plans To `Eradicate' Terrorists </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister on Plans To `Eradicate' Terrorists </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0304142194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1340 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0304142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Apr (MENA)--Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi 
has affirmed that the security agencies are keeping up their 
irreversible course in fighting terrorism without hesitation. 
He added that the Egyptian mass media have exposed what these 
groups are doing behind the scenes through the confessions of 
some of their members who came to their senses and returned to 
society's ranks. 
  Speaking at a celebration at the police academy today to 
mark 
the day of learning, al-Alfi said that these groups have plenty 
of secret undertakings, which will soon be publicized to expose 
the truth about this misguided bunch. 
  Al-Alfi added that the security agencies will not rest until 
they have eradicated the remnants of these terrorist elements 
who have turned terrorizing society into a profitable trade and 
way of life. 
  He emphasized that the security agencies are finished with 
the policy of action and reaction and will take the initiative 
to eradicate these elements in their hideouts to protect society. 
  During the celebration, excelling leaders and learners at 
the 
Interior Ministry were rewarded. 

</TEXT>

