<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily on Foreign Minister's Efforts To `Heal' Rift </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily on Foreign Minister's Efforts To `Heal' Rift </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0504103294 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 29 Mar 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> NC0504103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Abd-al-Nabi 'Abd-al-Sattar] </F>
  [Text] Iraqi Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf made 
intensive efforts on the sidelines of the Arab League Council 
session to persuade Arab countries, foremost Egypt, to normalize 
their relations with Iraq and allow the rift in Arab ranks to 
heal. 
  Al-Sahhaf met with the Egyptian, Jordanian, and Moroccan 
foreign ministers in a bid to improve Iraqi-Arab ties. Minister 
al-Sahhaf said that his country will be pleased to receive any 
Egyptian official who wishes to visit Baghdad in an attempt to 
normalize relations. 
  The Iraqi foreign minister accused Israel of arming and 
training the Kurds in Northern Iraq to destabilize the security 
and stability of Iraq. Al-Sahhaf called for a stiffer Arab 
boycott of Israel until the latter stops its arbitrary practices 
in the occupied territories and respects the resolutions of the 
UN Security Council and international legitimacy. 
  Al-Sahhaf said that his country implemented most UN Security 
Council resolutions. He denied that Iraq holds any Kuwaiti 
detainees, inviting Arab teams to visit Iraq to see for 
themselves. 

</TEXT>

