<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition: Envoys Recalled, New Security Council Formed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition: Envoys Recalled, New Security Council Formed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404180394 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan in 
Arabic 1530 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0404180394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Kurdistan </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry of the Saddam regime has 
recalled a number of ambassadors and heads of missions abroad to 
discuss urgent issues. This came in a circulation issued by the 
ministry a few days ago. The ministry is expected to discuss 
with these diplomats the method of action in the next phase. 
Iraqi opposition sources expect the regime to embark on 
diplomatic transfers on charges of dereliction of duties 
following the sharp criticism of Iraqi diplomacy made by 'Udayy 
Saddam Husayn through his newspaper BABIL. 
  An Iraqi diplomat, who asked to remain anonymous, revealed 
that a circular was issued by the Iraqi Intelligence Command to 
its offices in Iraqi embassies to activate their efforts and to 
contact Iraqis abroad to attract them to return to Iraq. 
  The intelligence office in the Iraqi regime embassy in 
Jordan 
embarked on an organized campaign to exert pressure on Iraqi 
writers, who are in Amman, to return to Iraq and to warn them 
against issuing any anti-regime writings. The source added that 
a ranking Iraqi intelligence officer, Hikmat al-Haju, joined the 
Amman Embassy staff to replace the second man in the embassy and 
to supervise intelligence activities together with two other 
employees who were assigned to the embassy earlier. The source 
added that a new plan has been set to utilize trade and 
commercial centers to collect information and to monitor the 
movements of Iraqis through recruiting agents among them as fake 
reporters and propagation employees who deal with Gulf papers. 
  In another development, Interior Minister Watban al-Tikriti, 
Saddam's half-brother, has been charged with the chairmanship of 
the Higher Council for National Security, including the heads of 
the Departments of Intelligence, Private Security, Military 
Intelligence, and Internal Public Security. This council will 
coordinate among the security departments and its affiliated 
institutions to tackle the emergency situation that is expected 
to explode in the country. 

</TEXT>

