<H3> <TI>   Iraq Protests U.S. Aircraft Violations to UN </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraq Protests U.S. Aircraft Violations to UN </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404114794 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0404114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraq has once again protested to the UN secretary 
general the U.S. aircraft violations of Iraqi airspace for 
observation, provocation purposes and for dropping flares. 
  Iraq's permanent represenative said in a memorandum 
addressed 
to the UN secretary general yesterday that the referent aircraft 
carried out 561 hostile air sorties and several reconnaissance 
sorties 21-30 April, in addition to dropping flares. 
  Iraq's permanent representative asked that the memorandum be 
circulated among the UN Security Council members and to consider 
it as one of its documents. 

</TEXT>

