<H3> <TI>   Security, Civilian Affairs Committees Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security, Civilian Affairs Committees Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Extremely Slow' Progress Reported </H4>

<F P=102> TA0404201694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 4 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the end of the second day of the deliberations 
of the military committee in Cairo, it transpires that the 
progress being made is extremely slow, despite public 
declarations on the intention to facilitate the talks and reach 
an agreement soon. Our correspondent in Cairo Arye Gus has 
learned that the Palestinians are avoiding agreements on various 
issues, and that they tried to reopen several issues which have 
already been concluded, such as the deployment of the 
Palestinian forces in Gaza and the timetable for the deployment 
of the police force in the autonomy areas. There are also 
differences between Israel and the PLO on the technical 
procedures for the entrance of the police force to the 
territories. Our correspondent was told that the Palestinians 
will not be given any responsibility over the autonomy areas 
before the agreement is signed, although they will be 
responsible for refugee camps handed over to them in these areas. 

</TEXT>

