<H3> <TI>   Security, Civilian Affairs Committees Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security, Civilian Affairs Committees Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th on Timetable for Entry of Police </H4>

<F P=102> NC0404205794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2020 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 4 Apr (MENA)--Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political 
adviser to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and chief of the 
Palestinian delegation to the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations 
to implement the Gaza-Jericho First agreement, has stated that 
today, the Phrasing Committee virtually completed the timetable 
for the entry of the police force to Gaza and Jericho and the 
details concerning its number, its jurisdiction, and powers. 
  Speaking to reporters following the working sessions that 
ended at 1930, Sha'th said: We are awaiting the Palestinian and 
Israeli leaderships' approval of some articles. 
  Commenting on reports of disagreements between the Israelis 
and Palestinians concerning the Palestinian police force, he 
said: I do not believe there are problems. We are talking 
about working out some details later on. 
  Sha'th said that no final agreement has been reached yet and 
that the two sides are awaiting the Palestinian and Israeli 
leaderships' approval of what has been reached. He added that 
negotiations will continue on the timetable for the entry of the 
police force, the nature of the force, and its armament. 
  The Palestinian and Israeli negotiators will resume their 
meetings in an hour. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

