<H3> <TI>   PFLP, DFLP on `Discrimination' in Deportees' Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFLP, DFLP on `Discrimination' in Deportees' Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404183694 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 4 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0404183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine 
[PFLP] and the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine 
[DFLP] issued two statements today in which they condemned the 
discrimination in the return of the Palestinian deportees. The 
two fronts noted that all the deportees who will return to the 
occupied territory are affiliated with the Fatah Movement and 
its supporters. 

</TEXT>

