<H3> <TI>   Security Officials Investigating Hotel Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Officials Investigating Hotel Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404090594 Amman Radio Jordan in English 0900 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0404090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fire has broken out briefly in Amman's Forte Grand 
Hotel, killing an Italian tourist and injuring at least 10 other 
people. Security officials were able to evacuate 430 people 
from the nine-story hotel and put down the blaze in a short 
period of time. 
  An Italian Embassy spokesman identified the dead tourist as 
(Michel Otorino). He had tried to escape the fire by jumping 
from the second story. Thick smoke reached the ninth floor and 
at least 10 people were hospitalized for broken limbs and smoke 
inhalation. Security officials are investigating the cause of 
the fire. The hotel is equipped by self-operated fire 
extinguishers, but were not used due to panic that gripped the 
hotel staff. 

</TEXT>

