<H3> <TI>   Rabin on Possibility of 'Arafat Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin on Possibility of 'Arafat Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0504071194 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0630 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0504071194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin said this morning 
that anyone who thought that the negotiations with the 
Palestinians could be concluded within a matter of days was 
wrong. Rabin said that there is no room for a meeting between 
himself and Yasir 'Arafat at the present time. 
  [Begin recording] [Rabin] Did anyone expect some kind of 
hocus-pocus? Anyone who thought that everything could be 
wrapped up within two or six days was simply wrong and did not 
understand the situation. If an agreement is not reached or, at 
least, until such an agreement is secured, we will have to 
clarify to the Palestinians how the economic side of things will 
be implemented. 
  [Economic affairs correspondent Shlomi Stein] In your 
opinion, is there room for another meeting between Yasir 'Arafat 
and yourself at the present time? 
  [Rabin] I think it is preferable to prepare such a meeting 
-- if and when it takes place -- in such a way as to preclude 
the possibility of another meeting between 'Arafat and myself 
ending unsuccessfully. [end recording] 
  Our economic affairs correspondent Shlomi Stein reports that 
the prime minister was speaking after a ceremony marking the 
sale of the Bet Shemesh engine factory to the Ormat company. 

</TEXT>

