<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Russia Coordinating With U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Russia Coordinating With U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0504115394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1030 GMT 5 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0504115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Yeltsin's envoy, Viktor Posuvalyuk, said 
he has been warmly received in Israel. In an interview with 
Jack Katzenell, Posuvalyuk said Russia is coordinating its 
Middle East policy with the United States. He dismissed the 
suggestion that Yasir 'Arafat is trying to exploit the 
traditional rivalry between the two superpowers to obtain last 
minute concessions from Israel. 
  [Begin recording] [Posuvalyuk] I think that Yasir 'Arafat 
adequately and in a right way understands that Russian cosponsor 
stands, let us say, in the middle between the two parties as the 
American cosponsor does. We are trying to help both parties. 
My concept is that the Israeli Government and the leadership of 
the PLO are in one boat. So, they are moving ahead with this 
peace process. They are helping each other, and they are serving 
their own interests. There is no contradiction. 
  [Katzenell] Have you had a warm welcome here in Israel? 
  [Posuvalyuk] Yes, yes. And I thank the Israeli Government 
for this warm welcome. 
  [Katzenell] What are you going to do next, sir? 
  [Posuvalyuk] I suppose in a few days, maybe -- in two or 
three days -- I am going to take part in Russian-American 
consultations on the Middle East. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

