<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres Meets Norwegian, Danish, Italian Envoys </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres Meets Norwegian, Danish, Italian Envoys </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404185994 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1700 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report followed by 'Imanu'el Rosen video </F>
report] 
  [Excerpt] The representatives of the Foreign and Defense 
ministries of the three countries which are contributing 
personnel to the international force in Hebron will arrive in 
Israel tomorrow. Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres today promised 
the Norwegian, Danish, and Italian ambassadors in Israel that 
the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] will guarantee the safety of the 
international force. Our political correspondent 'Imanu'el 
Rosen reports: 
  [Begin recording] [Rosen] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres 
today sought to assuage the concern of the ambassadors of the 
three countries which agreed to send observers to Hebron. For 
this reason he also summoned Major General Dani Yatom, the 
officer who will be in charge of the safety of the 160 
international observers as of next week. The complicated 
problems of coordination will be tackled, among other ways, by 
special uniforms and easily identified vehicles. Peres believes 
that the headache is not too bad: 
  [Peres] In English we refer to the temporary international 
presence in Hebron as TIPH, Temporary International Presence in 
Hebron [preceding five words in English]. In Hebrew we can 
refer to it as tipa [meaning one drop in Hebrew]. [passage 
omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

