<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Puts Off Discussion on Hebron Evacuation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Puts Off Discussion on Hebron Evacuation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404113894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 4 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In its session today, the cabinet decided not to 
discuss the evacuation of Jews from Hebron, and the ministers 
said that at this stage, the focus should be on promoting the 
negotiations on Gaza and Jericho. The cabinet heard optimistic 
briefings about the chances of concluding the negotiations with 
the Palestinians by the end of April. The prime minister 
expressed his fear that countries that pledged to contribute 
funds to the Palestinians might not transfer their donations in 
an orderly fashion, and that the delays might harm the residents 
of the territories and make the political process more difficult. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that the 
cabinet was briefed about the difficulties in the economic 
negotiations, due to disagreements among the Palestinians. The 
cabinet was further told that U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher will apparently arrive in the region toward the end 
of the month, before the resumption of the Washington 
negotiations. In his coming tour, he will also focus on 
promoting the negotiations with Syria. 

</TEXT>

