<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arabs Killed, Identified by IDF as Wanted Men </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arabs Killed, Identified by IDF as Wanted Men </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0404132294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 4 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The three terrorists killed in Hebron approximately 
10 days ago were involved in the murders of several Israelis in 
the territories. An IDF [Israel Defense Forces] spokesman 
reported that ballistic examinations of their weapons prove that 
the three men participated in the murders of Efrayim Ayubi, 
Shalom and Mordekhay Lapid, Me'ir Mendelovich, and Eliyahu 
Levin. They also participated in other terrorist attacks in 
which three Israeli citizens and six soldiers were wounded. 
  An Arab youth was captured this afternoon at the entrance to 
the Cave of the Patriarchs in possession of a knife, a 
switchblade knife, and a leaflet calling for revenge against the 
Jews. Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that the youth 
confessed he had planned to stab Jews. 
  Last night, the security forces discovered an arms cache 
containing a Kalashnikov rifle, a handgun, and a large quantity 
of ammunition, in Gaza city, near the home of a local resident, 
who is a Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] activist. Our 
correspondent Moti Amir reports that the man was detained for 
questioning. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

