Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0404163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the territories today, two Israeli civilians 
were wounded when their car was pelted with stones while passing 
through Bethlehem. One of them, lightly hurt, was treated by 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] medics on the spot; the other was 
evacuated to Hadassah Hospital where he is reported to be in 
moderate condition. 
  Meanwhile, Palestinian sources say up to 24 local residents 
were wounded in clashes with IDF troops today. The major flash 
points were reported to be in Hebron's old city, and in the town 
of Dayr al-Balah in the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

