<H3> <TI>   YSP Source Denies Oman Meeting Requested by al-Bid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Source Denies Oman Meeting Requested by al-Bid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404133594 Manama WAKH in Arabic 1300 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0404133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 4 Apr (WAKH)--A responsible source at the 
Central Committee of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] has denied 
that the Salalah meeting between President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
and his deputy 'Ali Salim al-Bid was held at al-Bid's request. 
  The source added that the Salalah meeting was the outcome of 
a proposal made by the Sultanate of Oman, Jordan, the United 
Arab Emirates, and Egypt, because the four countries were 
concerned that Yemen not slide into a civil war. The source 
went on to say that these countries advised the Yemenis and the 
Yemeni leaders to opt for either confederation or federation, 
particularly since the merger unity has failed due to doubts, 
suspicion, and mistrust between the two parties to the merger 
unity. 

</TEXT>

