<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Says Media Law To Be Issued `Soon' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Says Media Law To Be Issued `Soon' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404165194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister of State 'Ali 'Usayran has said the 
government will soon issue a law organizing the audio and visual 
media and will refer it to the Chamber of Deputies for 
ratification or amendment. 
  Speaking at his home in al-Rumaylah today, 'Usayran affirmed 
that the Chamber of Deputies is the defender of liberties. He 
added that the purpose of a media law is to organize the 
dissemination of political information, not to suppress 
liberties, especially as such suppression is a fruitless 
activity in Lebanon. 
  He pointed out that during the civil war the militias 
attempted to dictate their wishes to local communities. He 
explained that all those who lived through that period know that 
the silent majority in Lebanon opposed and still opposes any 
attempt to suppress liberties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

