<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief, Iraqi Minister Discuss Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Chief, Iraqi Minister Discuss Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404172894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1515 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 4 Apr (MENA)--Today Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid received Iraqi Labor Minister 
Latif Nusayyif Jasim, who is leading his country's delegation to 
the Arab Labor Conference in Cairo. 
  The Iraqi minister said that during his meeting with the 
secretary general they discussed Iraq's position regarding the 
UN Security Council's decision to extend the sanctions imposed 
on it. He pointed out that some Security Council members, 
including Russia and China, are inclined to lift these sanctions. 
  Jasim told reporters that the embargo on Iraq has deprived 
the citizens of basic commodities and services including some 
foodstuffs, medicines, electric power, and sewage systems. 

