<H3> <TI>   Yemen's Salih Comments on Visit Before Departure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's Salih Comments on Visit Before Departure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0404114194 Muscat Sultanate of Oman Television Network in 
Arabic 0900 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0404114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Muscat Sultanate of Oman Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] His Excellency Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council in fraternal Yemen, 
left the country this morning at the end of a two-day visit to 
the sultanate. 
  During the visit, his excellency the Yemeni leader held 
talks 
with His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id on fraternal relations, 
and ways to boost bilateral cooperation to serve and safeguard 
the interests of the two fraternal people. The discussions also 
dealt with the developments in the Republic of Yemen, and the 
sultanate's role in approximating viewpoints among the parties 
to the conflict in a manner that will safeguard the Republic of 
Yemen as a united entity, and the security and stability of the 
fraternal Yemeni people and all the people in the region. 
  The talks also dealt with issues of mutual interest and the 
developments on the regional and international level. [passage 
omitted] 
  His Excellency Lt. Gen 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih said he is 
pleased with the results of his visit to the sultanate and with 
the positive talks he held with His Majesty Sultan Qabus 
Bin-Sa'id and which were an opportunity to hold consultations on 
all that would enhance the fraternal and cordial relations 
between the two countries. 
  In a statement to the Oman News Agency, his excellency said: 
During this visit, we discussed the developments of the 
political crisis in our country in light of the good efforts his 
majesty the sultan is making in addition to many issues which 
are of interest to our two fraternal countries, the region, and 
the Arab nation. 
  His excellency said: I take this opportunity to reiterate 
thanks and appreciation in my name and on behalf of the Yemeni 
leadership, government, and people to the Sultanate of Oman -- 
leader, government, and people for the good offices it has been 
making to help us in Yemen overcome the crisis and the 
challenges it poses and safeguard the march of unity and 
stability in our country that will contribute to enhancing 
security, stability, and peace in the region. 
  Concluding his statement, his excellency said his country is 
eager to enhance relations of amity, cooperation, and 
coordination with the Sultanate of Oman because the eternal and 
solid bonds that exist between the two countries dictate that we 
preserve the ties of brotherhood and good neighborliness and 
work for constantly expanding the scopes of understanding and 
integration in the interest of both our people and Arab nation. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

