<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security, Civilian Affairs Committee Agendas Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security, Civilian Affairs Committee Agendas Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0504133194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1225 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0504133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 Mar (MENA)--Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political 
adviser to Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, and Major 
General Amnon Shahaq, Israeli deputy chief of staff, held a 
closed meeting this morning to discuss topics related to the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations currently being held in Cairo. 
  Earlier today, Palestinian and Israeli sources confirmed the 
existence of substantial differences between the two sides in 
the negotiations, particularly over the timetable for the 
withdrawal of Israeli troops, the entry of the Palestinian 
police force into Gaza and Jericho, and the arming of this force. 
  The meetings of the Security and Civilian Affairs Committees 
under the Gaza-Jericho Committee resumed this morning. The 
Security Committee is discussing a number of topics being 
disputed by the two sides, including the Palestinian police 
force's entry into the occupied territories, the exact size of 
the Jericho area, and the deployment of Palestinian forces in 
Gaza and Jericho. 
  The Civilian Affairs Committee is discussing the transfer of 
a number of powers, services, and utilities to the Palestinians 
as part of self-rule and in accordance with the 
Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of Principles signed in 
Washington on 13 September 1993. 

</TEXT>

