<H3> <TI>   PLO Reportedly To Open Office in Thailand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Reportedly To Open Office in Thailand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504193794 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 5 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brother Abu-al-Lutf [Faruq Qaddumi], acting 
chairman of the governing body of the Palestinian Economic 
Council for Development and Reconstruction, arrived in Vietnam 
yesterday for an official visit as part of his tour of Southeast 
Asia and China. Brother Abu-al-Lutf arrived in Hanoi after a 
three-day official visit to Bangkok during which he met 
Thailand's foreign minister. A spokesman for the Thai Foreign 
Ministry announced that agreement has been reached in principle 
between the PLO and Thailand on opening a PLO office in Bangkok. 
He said that the two sides have agreed on the opening of the 
office, but have not yet agreed on the details. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

