<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Leads Delegation on Visit to Amman </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further on Arrival Statement </H4>

<F P=102> JN0504170094 Amman PETRA-JNA in Arabic 1530 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0504170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman PETRA-JNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Amman, 5 Apr (PETRA)--Palestinian President 
Yasir 'Arafat arrived in Amman today on a visit to Jordan. 
[passage omitted] 
  On the resumption of talks with the Israelis, President 
'Arafat said: The talks are currently taking place. He added: 
Concerning the Arab-Israeli talks, they will be resumed soon. 
  Regarding the Jordanian-Palestinian Jerusalem Committee, 
which the two sides had earlier agreed to form, he said that the 
committee's work is not routine, but is related to an issue that 
is sacred to Arabs, Muslims, and Christians. 
  On his return to the autonomy region, the Palestinian 
president said: I am waiting. 
  Salim al-Za'nun, acting Palestine National Council speaker, 
arrived with President 'Arafat. 

</TEXT>

