<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Leads Delegation on Visit to Amman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Leads Delegation on Visit to Amman </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Coordination With Israel on Refugees Urged </H4>

<F P=102> JN0604061494 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0400 GMT 6 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0604061494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Jordanian side, led by His Majesty King Husayn, 
and the Palestinian side, led by President Yasir 'Arafat, held a 
meeting at the al-Hashimiyah Palace last night. His Highness 
Crown Prince Hasan and a number of officials from both sides 
attended. 
  His Majesty King Husayn emphasized Jordan's position in 
support of the Palestinian people's struggle, and toward easing 
the suffering of the kinsfolk in the occupied homeland in 
preparation for restoring their rights on their national soil. 
  For his part, President 'Arafat stressed the depth of 
relations between the two fraternal peoples, and expressed the 
Palestinian leadership and people's appreciation for Jordan's 
constant support for the Palestinian people's just cause and 
King Husayn's support for their struggle and national legitimate 
rights. 
  The two sides emphasized the importance of joint action on 
all issues of mutual concern, especially the peace process and 
the difficulties facing it. They stressed the importance of 
consultation and coordination between the Jordanian and 
Palestinian sides on one hand, and the Israeli side on the 
other, concerning the issue of refugees. 
  The two sides discussed activating previously formed 
Jordanian-Palestinian joint committees, which include the 
Jerusalem Committee, the Administrative Committee, and the 
Economic Committee. 
  On the Jordanian side, the meeting was attended by Dr. 
'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, prime minister; al-Sharif Zayd 
Bin-Shakir, Royal Hashemite Court chief; Marwan al-Qasim, 
political adviser to his majesty the king; Talal al-Hasan, 
minister of state for foreign affairs. 
  On the Palestinian side, the meeting was attended by Yasir 
'Abd-Rabbuh and Yasir 'Amr, PLO Executive Committee members; 
Salim al-Za'nun, acting Palestine National Council speaker; 
al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahim, Palestinian ambassador in Jordan; and 
Faysal al-Husayni. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-12110 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes066_m_94005" </HT>


