<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Deportees Return to West Bank, Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Deportees Return to West Bank, Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0504161794 Paris AFP in English 1514 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0504161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jericho, Occupied West Bank, April 5 (AFP) -- 
Twenty-six Palestinians who were exiled by Israel returned to 
the occupied territories on Tuesday [5 April] to bolster 
preparations for self-rule, military officials said. 
  The group, nearly all from PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat's 
Fatah 
movement, crossed the Allenby Bridge from Jordan at the second 
attempt after the Israeli authorities at first refused to accept 
23 of their 46 relatives. 
  The officials said the group had completed formalities, been 
issued identity cards and would shortly pass out of the Israeli 
side of the border post. 
  Another couple of dozen Palestinians were being processed at 
the Rafah border crossing from Egypt into the Gaza Strip 
following a deal between Israel and the PLO in Cairo last 
Thursday. 
  Of the 26, one is a communist, one independent and one from 
Yasir Abd-Rabbuh's moderate Fida' group. 
  The rest are Fatah men considered vital to efforts to build 
autonomy in Gaza and the West Bank town of Jericho. 
  The exiles were expelled or wanted by the Israeli 
authorities 
and had fled abroad since Israel seized the territories in 1967. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-12125 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes066_l_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-066 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  6 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

