<H3> <TI>   Observers Said To Deploy in Hebron `Next Week' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Observers Said To Deploy in Hebron `Next Week' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0504150494 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1230 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0504150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The multinational observers will apparently begin 
deploying in Hebron next week, Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres 
determined today after meeting for the first time with 
representatives of the countries participating in the force. 
The foreign minister added that the 160 observers from Italy, 
Denmark, and Norway will mainly engage in administrative duties: 
60 of them will report on the situation in the field directly 
to the Israeli security forces, and the other 100 will advise 
the Israeli Government and Hebron Municipality in a bid to 
attain a normalization of the situation in the city. 

</TEXT>

