<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Attorney General Submits Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Attorney General Submits Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0504131994 Islamabad THE NEWS in English 5 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BK0504131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad THE NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad -- Within twenty four hours of the 
resignation of Attorney General [AG] Fakhruddin G Ibrahim, 
Deputy Attorney General Mumtaz Ali Mirza too has submitted his 
resignation to President Farooq Leghari. 
  "I don't want to say anything other than that I have 
resigned," the rather cautious Mumtaz Ali remarked when asked 
about reasons of resignation. 
  The move of the Deputy AG, viewed as a setback to the 
government, comes at a time when serious efforts are being 
apparently made by the top government officials to persuade 
Fakhruddin G. Ibrahim to withdraw his previous decision. 
  In his resignation letter, sent to the President, Mirza 
says, 
"I regret to say that it is no longer possible for me to 
continue as Deputy AG. Accordingly, I tender my resignation. 
You are informed." Government circles refused to comment on 
the resignation. 

</TEXT>

