<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Libyan Foreign Minister Arrives on 2-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Libyan Foreign Minister Arrives on 2-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Foreign Minister </H4>

<F P=102> BK0404162694 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0404162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan and Libya have held wide-ranging talks on 
a number of bilateral and international issues, including 
Kashmir, Bosnia, the situation in Afghanistan, Palestine, and 
Central Asia. The talks were held in Islamabad today between the 
foreign minister, Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, and his Libyan 
counterpart, Mr. 'Umar Mustafa al-Muntasir. The foreign 
minister of Libya was conveyed the gratitude of the Government 
and people of Pakistan for the assurances given by the Libyan 
leader Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi for full support to Pakistan on 
Kashmir. 
  The Libyan foreign minister was informed about Pakistan's 
efforts to promote an amicable solution to the issue of UN 
sanctions against Libya. The two foreign ministers also 
deliberated on issues about the ratification of the draft 
administrative procedures relating to the social security 
agreement between Pakistan and Libya, payment of disability 
pension to Pakistani workers, release of outstanding payments of 
various Pakistani concerns by Libya, and possibility of export 
of Pakistani manpower to Libya. 
  The issue of enhancing economic cooperation between the two 
countries also came up for discussion. The two sides agreed 
that the joint ministerial commission should be held at an early 
date. 

</TEXT>

