<H3> <TI>   Paper `Cast Doubt' on Armed Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper `Cast Doubt' on Armed Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0404174994 Cairo MENA in English 1700 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0404174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 4 Apr (MENA)--The Sudanese authorities 
today suspended AL-SUDANI AL-DUWALI newspaper. The decision was 
taken under the emergency laws. 
  A statement by the Sudanese Presidency, carried by Omdurman 
radio today, said that the paper cast doubt on the struggle of 
the Sudanese Armed Forces and called for separation and 
abandoning the unity of the country and disintegrating national 
unity. It also dealt lightly with the prestige of the 
revolution and its symbols without any justification. 

</TEXT>

