<H4>    Pan-Arab Issues Discussed </H4>

<F P=102> JN0504115894 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0504115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo -- President Hafiz al-Asad and President 
Muhammad Husni Mubarak resumed talks in a closed meeting held at 
the permanent headquarters of the Egyptian Presidency in Cairo 
at 1115 Damascus time [0815 GMT] today. 
  Talks dealt with the Arab situation, inter-Arab relations in 
light of the current developments and circumstances, and the 
importance of working to improve inter-Arab relations and for an 
Arab solidarity that serves both the Arab nation's pan-Arab 
interest and the pan-Arab issues. 

</TEXT>

