<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 Apr (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
stressed that a full Israeli withdrawal from the Golan would 
mean a peace agreement between the Syrian and Israeli sides 
could be reached. In a statement he made today, Musa added: I 
believe that everybody agrees on this. 
  Asked if he thinks progress could be made on the 
Syrian-Israeli track following Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad's 
visit to Egypt that ended today, Musa said: Naturally, on the 
basis of land for peace. 
  Minister Musa was asked if this means that the ball is now 
in 
the Israeli court, he said: As far as the Israeli withdrawal is 
concerned, the ball is indeed in the Israeli court now. 

