<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qatari Parliament Speaker Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qatari Parliament Speaker Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Nateq-Nuri </H4>

<F P=102> LD0504110494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The speaker of the Qatari parliament arrived in 
Tehran today at the head of a parliamentary delegation. He was 
welcomed at the airport by Mr. 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri, the Majles 
speaker. 
  Mr. 'Ali bin-Khalifa al-Hatm said in an interview with our 
reporter that the purpose of his visit to Iran was to expand 
relations even further and said the visit was of importance to 
his country's officials. 
  Mr. Nateq-Nuri, for his part, spoke in an interview with our 
reporter about issues that will be discussed in talks between 
the two countries' officials. 
  [Begin Nateq-Nuri recording] We will discuss economic 
issues, 
such as the issue of the transfer of potable water to Qatar, 
which is a very huge project; the exploitation of a joint gas 
field; and regional issues and issues relating to the world of 
Islam and Islamic countries, such as the issue of Palestine and 
so on. Our relations with Qatar are very sincere, warm, and 
long-standing. Qatar has consistently adopted very good stances 
in international organizations -- during the imposed Iran-Iraq 
war for example -- and this kind of thing means our relations 
with Qatar are on a special footing and of importance to us. 
God willing, we hope that, with this visit by these gentlemen, 
these relations will expand even further. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

