<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tehran To Help GCC Clean Oil Spill </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tehran To Help GCC Clean Oil Spill </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0304103794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0304103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Environmental Protection Organization has 
announced that the oil spill resulting from the collision of two 
oil tankers in the Gulf of Oman is moving in a southerly 
direction and poses no threat to the coastline of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran. 
  According to an IRNA report, the official in charge of 
research of the Environmental Protection Organization announced 
Iran's readiness to cooperate with the Persian Gulf Cooperation 
Council [GCC] and other international environmental protection 
organizations in order to clean up this oil spill and said: The 
spill is moving in a southerly direction on the Sea of Oman from 
a point east of the Straits of Hormuz. 

</TEXT>

