<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Rejects U.S. Charge on Drugs Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Envoy Rejects U.S. Charge on Drugs Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604102994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our country's permanent representative to the United 
Nations described as deceitful the remarks made by U.S. State 
Department officials about Iran's performance in the fight 
against narcotics. 
  He stressed: While Iran has come under strong Western 
criticism for taking strict antinarcotics measures, the United 
States accuses Tehran of procrastination in the matter. 
  Referring to data and statistics and a report by the 
International Narcotics Control Board, our country's permanent 
UN representative said: The Islamic Republic of Iran has taken 
extensive measures to control narcotics, not only in the region 
but also globally. Tehran's investment in the matter is of the 
highest level. 
  The U.S. assistant secretary of state claimed last Monday 
that the Islamic Republic of Iran is taking no measures to fight 
narcotics smuggling. 

</TEXT>

