<H3> <TI>   Chinese Official Calls Iranian Relations `Unique' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Official Calls Iranian Relations `Unique' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0204165394 Tehran IRNA in English 1619 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0204165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 2, IRNA -- Chinese Vice Premier and 
Minister of Foreign Affairs Qian Qichen in his meeting on Friday 
the with Iranian ambassador here, Mohammad-Hoseyn Mirfakhar, 
expressed hope that the developing countries would expand their 
ties despite the pressures put by the big Western powers. 
  He said Tehran-Beijing relations were "unique" and that the 
two countries pursued independent policies. 
  Mirfakhar referring to common interests expressed hope that 
with expansion of bilateral ties a new phase can be opened in 
Iran-China ties. 
  At the end of the meeting, Qian assessed the outcome of his 
last "satisfactory". 

</TEXT>

