BFN 

  [Text] Doha, 5 Apr (WAKH)--A round of official talks was 
held in Doha this morning between His Highness Shaykh Khalifah 
Bin-Hamad Al Thani, amir of Qatar, and Yemeni President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih. The meeting was attended by His Highess Shaykh 
Hamad Bin-Khalifah Al Thani, Qatar's heir apparent, and senior 
officials from both countries. 
  The Qatari News Agency noted that the talks dealt with the 
situation in Yemen, [words indistinct], the peace process in the 
Middle East, and the overall Arab and regional developments. 
The two leaders also exchanged views on ways to reinforce Arab 
solidarity and consolidate and develop bilateral relations. 
  The Yemeni president left Doha today following a two-day 
visit to Qatar. He was seen off at the airport by His Highness 
Shaykh Khalifah Bin-Hamad Al Thani, amir of Qatar, and senior 
Qatari officials. 

