<H3> <TI>   Zayid, Yemen's al-Bid Discuss Yemeni Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zayid, Yemen's al-Bid Discuss Yemeni Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0304104294 Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network in 
Arabic 0930 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0304104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, 
the head of state, received at the Rawdat al-Rif rest house this 
morning Mr. 'Ali Salim al-Bid, deputy chairman of the 
Presidential Council in the Republic of Yemen. Al-Bid briefed 
his highness on the latest developments of the Yemeni situation 
and efforts to end the political crisis. Views were exchanged 
on current Arab developments. 
  His highness the head of state emphasized his concern for 
Yemen's stability and national unity. His highness said: Our 
care for our brothers and kinsfolk in Yemen is equal to our care 
for our own people and country. He added: Contributions from 
any of our brothers toward solving problems in Yemen deserve all 
appreciation and respect from his brothers because Yemen's 
stability and security is in the interest of all. 
  For his part, 'Ali Salim al-Bid praised his highness' 
pan-Arab stands, wise leadership, positive initiative, and 
continuous efforts for the progress and safety of the Arab 
nation in general and Yemen in particular. Al-Bid said: We 
have come to you fully confident of your efforts and endeavors 
of which we are proud in order to serve Yemen and its progress. 
  The meeting was attended by His Highness Sultan Bin-Zayid Al 
Nuhayyan, the deputy prime minister; His Highness Lieutenant 
General Muhammad Bin-Zayid Al Nuhayyan, the chief of staff of 
the Armed Forces; His Highness Hamdan Bin-Zayid Al Nuhayyan, 
minister of state for foreign affairs; and Khamis Bayk 
al-Rumaythi, director of President Zayid's office. 

</TEXT>

