<H3> <TI>   Reports on Salih-al-Bid Meeting Termed `Inaccurate' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Salih-al-Bid Meeting Termed `Inaccurate' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0504204294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0504204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has stated to the Yemeni News 
Agency, SABA', that a number of news agencies and newspapers 
have carried inaccurate reports on the proceedings of the 
meetings that took place in the Omani city of Salalah between 
brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential 
Council chairman, and brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice chairman 
of the Presidential Council, in the presence of His Majesty 
Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id of Oman, and the subsequent bilateral 
meeting between the brother chairman of the Presidential Council 
and his deputy. The source regretted the unjustified confusion 
and anxiety that those incorrect reports have caused among the 
public. The source indicated that although those meetings did 
not emerge with the results that all Yemenis had looked forward 
to, they did help stress the need to abide by the pledge and 
accord document and to swiftly implement the decisions that the 
Council of Ministers made during its meetings in the economic 
and trade capital [Aden], especially regarding security and 
military issues. 

</TEXT>

