<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Car Bomb Explodes in 'Afula; Death Toll Rising </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Car Bomb Explodes in 'Afula; Death Toll Rising </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Preliminary Report Says 5 Dead, 36 Injured </H4>

<F P=102> LD0604111194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1030 GMT 6 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] First to 'Afula where a car bomb exploded three 
meters from a bus. Latest reports say five people were killed, 
another 35 at least wounded. The incident occurred near a 
cultural center. Apparently there was a suicide bomber in the 
car. Neil Samba has the story. Neil: 
  [Samba] The explosion occurred at around 1230 near the 
cultural center of 'Afula not far from the town's ... er, in the 
center of the 'Afula, not far from the town's main auditorium. 
Latest reports speak of five dead and 35 injured, but these 
figures are changing and constantly being updated. Reports from 
[words indistinct] say that the injuries range from light to 
serious. Some of the injured were on the bus and others were 
waiting at a nearby bus station. All of the injured are being 
taken to the (?Haemic) hospital. The evacuation continues at 
this hour. We've just heard though that two of those seriously 
injured were taken to Haifa, Haifa's Rambam hospital. Northern 
district police commander Jacob Grenel was the first to confirm 
that it was in fact a car bomb that exploded near an Egged bus, 
but he said it's not clear whether it was a suicide bomber or 
whether the bomb was set off by remote control. 
  The explosion took place three to four meters from a bus 
stop. [passage omitted]. Dozens of ambulances arrived on the 
scene within minutes after the explosion and the police closed 
off the area. Police reinforcements were sent into the town and 
engineers are combing the area. The center of 'Afula has been 
closed off. [passage omitted] A lot of details are still 
unclear at this time. 

</TEXT>

