<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Begins Legal Action Against Closed Daily </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0504221094 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
English 1800 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0504221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The justice minister and attorney general, 
'Abd-al-Aziz Shiddu, has directed the supreme prosecution 
attorney in Khartoum State to adopt legal procedures regarding 
violation of the daily AL-SUDAN AL-DUWALI of Section No. 6 of 
the penal code related to circulation of false news. He also 
directed the concerned authorities to conduct preliminary 
investigations of some of the issues published by the daily. 
  He underlined that those who raised claims on corruption and 
malpractices at the state government institutions will be 
required to prove their claim . On application of the emergency 
law against the daily, Shiddu said that the law is valid in 
spite of the fact that it has not been applied in many cases in 
the past period so as to ensure stability of the political 
system. 

