<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Media Comment Before ESCAP Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials, Media Comment Before ESCAP Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Commerce Secretary Notes GATT Stand </H4>

<F P=102> BK0404135594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0404135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The golden jubilee session of the Economic and 
Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific [ESCAP] begins in New 
Delhi tomorrow. At a joint press briefing with the ESCAP 
executive secretary in New Delhi today, the commerce secretary, 
Mr. Tejinder Khanna, said India will voice its concern at the 
meeting over any form of neoprotectionist measures in the 
post-Uruguay round of Trade and Tariff Agreement. He said we 
would not like any alibis to be trotted out to serve as a 
roadblock to global trade. The ESCAP executive secretary, Mr. 
Rafiuddin Ahmad, described the new GATT deal as a package of 
mutual benefit. He, however, said the member countries have to 
be watchful against any kind of protectionism and ensure that 
the agreement is implemented in letter and spirit. 

</TEXT>

