Daily Report 
<DATE1>  5 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Businessman Reportedly Dies in `Planned' Accident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Businessman Reportedly Dies in `Planned' Accident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0504195694 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 5 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0504195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Iraqi Broadcasting Corporation, a body 
affiliated with the Iraqi National Congress, which is composed 
of organizations opposing the Iraqi regime, has said that 
Al-Hajj 'Abd-al-Latif al-Hajj Mahmud Bunniyah was killed in an 
accident planned against his car while he was traveling to 
Jordan. The corporation said that Bunniyah, who is from one of 
the most important merchant families in Iraq, had recently 
criticized Baghdad's financial policy which led to the 
deterioration of the Iraqi dinar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
